18:T9c9,<h2>First Impressions</h2><p>Arriving at NAC Nueva Alcántara for the first time, you immediately understand why this club has become the benchmark for padel in southern Spain. The complex sprawls across several acres in the San Pedro Alcántara urbanisation, with 16 courts — a mix of indoor and outdoor — visible from the entrance. The facility is immaculately maintained, and the energy is palpable from the moment you walk through the doors.</p><h2>The Courts</h2><p>NAC's courts are divided between a climate-controlled indoor hall housing six courts and ten outdoor courts surrounded by tall fencing and floodlights for evening play. All surfaces are premium artificial grass in excellent condition, replaced on a strict rotation schedule to ensure consistent bounce and traction. The outdoor courts benefit from the club's sheltered location, which reduces wind interference even on breezy coastal days.</p><ul><li>6 indoor courts (climate controlled, LED lighting)</li><li>10 outdoor courts (floodlit until 23:00)</li><li>All courts: premium artificial grass, Agility brand</li><li>Glass walls: 10mm tempered, exceptional rebound consistency</li></ul><h2>Facilities and Amenities</h2><p>The clubhouse is a modern, spacious building housing changing rooms with high-quality showers, a fully-stocked pro shop, a physiotherapy clinic, and a restaurant-bar that serves proper food until late. The bar area is particularly lively after matches, with a genuine community feel that you don't always find at larger clubs. The pro shop stocks all the major padel brands with knowledgeable staff who can help you find the right equipment.</p><h2>Coaching and Programmes</h2><p>NAC's coaching academy is one of the finest on the Costa del Sol. Led by former WPT professional Javier Morales, the team of six coaches offers group clinics for all levels, private lessons, and a junior academy that has produced several nationally ranked players. The weekly social ladder tournament on Wednesday evenings is particularly well organised and a great way to meet other players at your level.</p><h2>Value and Booking</h2><p>Court hire runs from €18 to €28 per hour depending on the time slot and whether you choose indoor or outdoor. By Marbella standards this is extremely competitive given the quality on offer. Booking through Playtomic is smooth and reliable, and the club's staff are responsive via WhatsApp for any queries. NAC deserves its reputation as the best all-round padel club in Marbella.</p>15:["$","section",null,{"className":"bg-sand-light py-16","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"font-heading text-2xl font-bold text-navy mb-8","children":"More in Club Reviews"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6","children":[["$","$L17","nac-nueva-alcantara-review",{"post":{"slug":"nac-nueva-alcantara-review","title":"NAC Nueva Alcántara: An In-Depth Review of Marbella's Best Padel Club","excerpt":"We spent a full week at NAC Nueva Alcántara to bring you the most thorough review of Marbella's largest and most acclaimed padel complex.","category":"Club Reviews","date":"2026-02-20","readTime":9,"author":"María González","coverImage":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1560012057-4372e14c5085?w=800&q=80&auto=format&fit=crop","content":"$18"}}]]}]]}]}]
